  "title": "Amazon Q1 2025 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2025-05-01T21:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2025_Q1",
  "location": "Seattle, WA",
  "url": "https://ir.aboutamazon.com/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "andy-jassy",
      "speaker_name": "Andy Jassy",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "AWS had an extraordinary Q1. Revenue grew 17% to $29.3 billion and we see no signs of deceleration. Demand for AI infrastructure continues to outstrip our capacity to build it. We have committed to investing over $100 billion in infrastructure in 2025, the largest single-year capital commitment in our history. Amazon Bedrock now powers AI applications for over 10,000 active enterprise customers. We expect AWS to surpass $120 billion in annual revenue in 2025."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "brian-olsavsky",
      "speaker_name": "Brian Olsavsky",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:20:00",
      "text": "Total net sales were $155.7 billion, up 9% year-over-year. AWS operating income was $11.5 billion, with a margin of 39.3%. Advertising revenue grew 19% to $13.9 billion. North America retail operating income was $5.9 billion. We are guiding Q2 net sales to $159–164 billion and expect AWS growth to remain in the mid-to-high teens."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:38:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Mark Mahaney at Evercore ISI."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-mark-mahaney",
      "speaker_name": "Mark Mahaney",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:38:20",
      "text": "Andy, $100 billion in capex is a very bold commitment. How confident are you in the return timeline, and does it change your thinking on free cash flow for 2025?"
    }
  ],
